This paper is about a model-based algorithm for recovering word boundaries in natural-language text, which falls under the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The algorithm is derived from a probability model, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of minimum description length (MDL), which is a common technique in information theory and compression, suggesting a possible connection to systems and control (cs.SD) and computing and society (cs.CC).
